<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-22T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-22T21:00:00-05:00" n="570" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/872: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-22T22:00:00-04:00">October
                                    22, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>544. We think that agreements for Military and <hi rend="italic">Gendarmerie</hi> missions should be included in pending matters
                            demanding immediate attention listed in your 1007, October 19.</p>
                        <pb facs="0560" n="548" xml:id="pg_548"/>
                        <p>McDonnell yesterday declined to accept position of pharmaceutical
                            director. We will try to find another man promptly.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>